\begin{abstract}
We formalize the Nexus Fusion Model as a nonlinear controlled dynamical system with a triple-product threshold, local nonlinear stability, optimal-control necessary conditions, and a verification-oriented finite-state abstraction. Sufficient conditions for forward invariance, reachability, and boundedness are established.
\end{abstract}
\section{Introduction}
The Nexus Fusion Model is a three-state nonlinear control system with threshold-defined operating modes. Its core performance functional is the triple product
\[
\Phi(x)=EN\tau.
\]
